We want to express this in terms of product constructions:
// defined as d(x, x') = sum_i d_{inner}(x_i, x'_i), where x_i is the ith partition
struct ProductMetric<M> { _inner: PhantomData<M> }
impl<M> Metric for ProductMetric<M> {
    type Distance = M::Distance;
    ...
}

struct ProductDomain<D> { inner_domains: Vec<D> }
impl<D> Domain for ProductDomain<D> {
    type Carrier = Vec<D::Carrier>;
}
We need the ProductDomain because we still want to allow some variability in the domain of each partition (for instance, in dataset size). However, this design does not allow the dataset in each partition to vary in structure.
We can still allow the dataset/query to vary within each partition by applying different transformations to each partition.
